Liverpool have completed the signing Portugal international Diogo Jota from Wolves. The Premier League champions have announced the 23-year-old has signed a “long-term” contract at Anfield. The deal comes a day after the Reds signed Thiago Alcantara from European champions Bayern Munich. It’s time… #JotaSaturday <img src="https://i1.wp.com/s.w.org/images/core/emoji/11/72x72/1f929.png?ssl=1" alt="🤩" data-recalc-dims="1"/> pic.twitter.com/2Z8Tav8lBw — Liverpool FC (@LFC) September 19, 2020 The forward has caught the eye over the last three seasons at Molineux, two of which have seen the club in the Premier League. Jota told the club’s website, www.liverpoolfc.com: “It’s just a really exciting moment for me and my family. “All of my path since I was a kid and now, to join a club like Liverpool – the world champions – is just unbelievable. I just want to get started.” Jota claimed the move was one he could not turn down. Read: Thiago? Jota? Liverpool have smashed this window He said: “When you look at the Premier League, you always see Liverpool as one of the biggest teams in the country, so it’s impossible to say no. “So we just want to come (to the club), to give our best and hopefully I can become a good option for Liverpool in the future.” Photo courtesy of @LFC on Twitter  The post Diogo Jota ‘couldn’t say no’ as Liverpool confirm new signing appeared first on Football365. Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.